HEADWORD: Benzamide
<hw>Ben*zam"ide</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Benz</ets>oin + <ets>amide</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>A transparent crystalline substance, <chform>C6H5.CO.NH2</chform>,
obtained by the action of ammonia upon chloride of benzoyl, as also by
several other reactions with benzoyl compounds.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Benzene</ent>⟦br⟧
